      "conditioning_notes": "`<CHAR_A>`'s love of breaking the pattern and fear of being taken seriously drives every beat — they undercut `<CHAR_B>`'s analysis, volunteer chaos as strategy, and flinch when `<CHAR_B>` correctly frames their unpredictability as a pattern. The moment they need \"a minute\" in narreme_005 is the fear surfacing: being legible is the one thing they can't handle. `<CHAR_B>`'s love of seeing the pattern first and fear of being wrong in public shapes the quiet devastation when `<CHAR_A>` names the hand-thing — `<CHAR_B>` goes silent because being read correctly is exactly what they dread. The Arena location means neither character can fully drop the performance; every exchange has an audience function even when the two of them are just talking at each other. `<CHAR_C>` is the constant underneath: not resolving anything, just maintaining. Snacks before. Snacks after. The group still exists because of the person holding the `<PROP_A>` and memorizing who needs what. Tension stays within 1–3 across all eight beats but traces a genuine rise — social stakes accumulate even at low dial settings because the Arena makes every small observation feel like testimony."
